# The single source of truth is plan.md. Everything below is local working
# material — regenerable, large, or reference — and is intentionally untracked.
papers/
data_gen/
rtl/
picorv32/
picorv32/runs/
**/__pycache__/
*.log
paperCodes/
datasets/
cache/*
# EXCEPTION — cache/coords is the one cache that is NOT regenerable everywhere: it is derived
# from datasets/sky130hd/gates (2.8GB), which is not on the cluster, and rsync through the
# double jump host is not workable. So it ships via git. Kept small on purpose (float16, 43MB).
# Everything else under cache/ stays untracked — it can be rebuilt from the dataset in place.
!cache/coords/
# EXCEPTION 2 — cache/fp_arrival, same reason, WORSE. It is derived from
# datasets/sky130hd/timing_paths (30GB — ten times the gates table that already forced this
# exception). scripts/add_fp_arrival.py cannot run on the cluster: the table is not there.
# It is 2.5MB — 18x smaller than coords — so shipping it is free.
# CAUGHT BY: seam_2x2's own guard, which would have hard-failed every job at second 5
# (NC=0 != NG=1944). The guard worked; the cache plan did not.
!cache/fp_arrival/
venv/
*.tar.gz

# Results: COMMIT the logs + metrics (so we can pull them off the cluster with git pull),
# but NEVER the model weights — a .pt is ~2MB x 9 tasks and would bloat the repo forever.
runs/**/*.pt
